The White House has released a statement regarding the situation in Egypt, urging all parties to avoid violence and calling on the Egyptian authorities to respond peacefully to any protests. The statement emphasizes the support for the universal rights of the Egyptian people, including freedom of expression, association, and assembly. The Egyptian government is encouraged to take this opportunity to meet the aspirations of the Egyptian people and pursue political, economic, and social reforms. The United States is committed to working with Egypt towards these goals. The statement also highlights the belief that all people desire certain things, such as the ability to express themselves, have a say in governance, and live freely, and that these are human rights that should be supported everywhere.